<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idef7a779c-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s2254c"><num value="2254c">§ 2254c.</num><heading> Research</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There is appropriated, out of any funds in the Treasury not otherwise appropriated, $20,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2021 and 2022 for the Agricultural Research Service to address gaps in nutrition research at the critical intersections of responsive agriculture, quality food production, and human nutrition and health.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idef7a779d-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/116/260/dN/tVII/s756">Pub. L. 116–260, div. N, title VII, § 756</ref>, <date date="2020-12-27">Dec. 27, 2020</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/134/2109">134 Stat. 2109</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/117/158/s4/c">Pub. L. 117–158, § 4(c)</ref>, <date date="2022-06-25">June 25, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/1312">136 Stat. 1312</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idef7a779e-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idef7a779f-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idef7a77a0-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2022—<ref href="/us/pl/117/158">Pub. L. 117–158</ref> substituted “for each of fiscal years 2021 and 2022” for “for fiscal year 2021 and each fiscal year thereafter”.</p>
</note>
